WITH agents AS (
    SELECT IsActive
      ,CreatedBy
      ,DateCreated
      ,LastUpdated
      ,LastUpdatedBy
      ,isSentToDavidCard
      ,Notes
      ,AgentID
      ,AgentParentID
      ,AgentGroupId
      ,AgentTypeId
      ,InsuranceCompanyID
      ,AgencyID
      ,FirstName
      ,LastName
      ,EnglishFirstName
      ,EnglishMiddleName
      ,EnglishLastName
      ,PersonalID
      ,CustomerFileManagerId
      ,HasAffiliateIdInSite
      ,SalesManagerId
      ,AgentCommissionEmail
      ,EMailAddress
      ,Policy_Types_MainID
      ,AllowContactWithCustomersByDS
    FROM {{ ref('stg_bronze__mrr_agents') }}
),
params_not_real_agent AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT param_value_num AS agentid
    FROM {{ ref('stg_mng__mng_params') }}
    WHERE param_name = 'NoRealAgent'
),
params_is_natbag AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT param_value_num AS agentid
    FROM {{ ref('stg_mng__mng_params') }}
    WHERE param_name = 'Natbag'
),
pod_agreements AS (
    SELECT 
        objectid AS agentid, 
        MIN(datecreated) AS FirstPODAgreementDate
    FROM {{ ref('stg_bronze__mrr_dc_pod_agreements') }}
    WHERE objectypeid = 5
    GROUP BY objectid
)

SELECT 
    a.*,
    CASE WHEN pna.agentid IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS not_real_agent,
    CASE WHEN pnb.agentid IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_natbag,
    pod.FirstPODAgreementDate
    ,getdate() as dwh_date_created
    ,getdate() as dwh_date_updated
FROM agents a
LEFT JOIN params_not_real_agent pna ON a.agentid = pna.agentid
LEFT JOIN params_is_natbag pnb ON a.agentid = pnb.agentid
LEFT JOIN pod_agreements pod ON a.agentid = pod.agentid

WITH policy_coverage AS (
    SELECT * FROM {{ ref('fact_policy_coverage') }}
),

policies AS (
    SELECT * FROM {{ ref('fact_policies') }}
),

policy_status AS (
    SELECT * FROM {{ ref('dim_policy_status') }}
),

policy_groups AS (
    SELECT * FROM {{ ref('dim_policy_groups') }}
),

benefits AS (
    SELECT * FROM {{ ref('dim_benefits') }}
),

policy_discount AS (
    SELECT CoverageId, SUM(Pct) AS pct
    FROM {{ ref('fact_policy_discount') }}
    WHERE CAST(IsActive AS INT) = 1
    GROUP BY CoverageId
),

policy_discount_updated AS (
    SELECT CoverageId
    FROM {{ ref('fact_policy_discount') }}
    WHERE LastUpdated IS NOT NULL
),

uw_exclusion_codes AS (
    SELECT last_uw.DecisionID, last_uw.ExclusionCodeId, last_uw.UW_Pct, last_uw.LastUpdated
    FROM (
        SELECT fuec2.DecisionID, fuec2.ExclusionCodeId, fuec2.UW_Pct, fuec2.LastUpdated,
               RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY fuec2.DecisionID ORDER BY COALESCE(fuec2.LastUpdated, fuec2.DateCreated) DESC) AS rnk
        FROM {{ ref('fact_uw_exclusion_codes') }} fuec2
        WHERE CAST(fuec2.IsActive AS INT) = 1
    ) AS last_uw
    WHERE last_uw.rnk = 1
),

params AS (
    SELECT * 
    FROM {{ ref('stg_mng__mng_params') }}
    where param_subject = 'BenefitBand'
)

SELECT DISTINCT 
    fpc.PolicyID,
    fp.Member_ID,
    fp.TravelPolicyNumber,
    fp.PolicyStartDate,
    fp.PolicyEndDate,
    fp.StatusID AS policy_status_id,
    pp.Status_Eng AS policy_status_name,
    fpc.IsPeriodicRider,
    fpc.IdPolicy,
    dpg.PolicyName,
    dpg.IsAnnual,
    fpc.CoverageId,
    fpc.BenefitId,
    db.BenefitName,
    CASE 
        WHEN CAST(db.IsReider AS INT) = 0 OR mp.param_name = 'Base' THEN 'Base Plan' 
        ELSE db.BenefitName 
    END AS calc_benefit_type,

    fpc.Cov_Start_Date,
    fpc.Cov_End_Date,
    fpc.StatusId AS coverage_status_id,
    maps.Status_Eng AS coverage_status_name,

    CASE 
        WHEN CAST(dpg.IsPolicyRider AS INT) = 1 THEN 0
        ELSE 1
    END *
    CASE 
        WHEN CAST(db.IsReider AS INT) = 1 THEN 0
        ELSE 1
    END *
    CASE 
        WHEN CAST(dpg.IsAnnual AS INT) = 1 THEN 60.000 / 365.000
        ELSE 1
    END *
    (
        CASE 
            WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, fpc.Cov_Start_Date, fpc.Cov_End_Date) + 1 <= 0 THEN 1
            ELSE DATEDIFF(DAY, fpc.Cov_Start_Date, fpc.Cov_End_Date) + 1
        END
    ) AS base_days,

    CASE 
        WHEN CAST(db.IsReider AS INT) = 1 AND mp.param_name <> 'Base' THEN 1
        ELSE 0
    END *
    CASE 
        WHEN CAST(dpg.IsAnnual AS INT) = 1 THEN 60.000 / 365.000
        ELSE 1
    END *
    (
        CASE 
            WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, fpc.Cov_Start_Date, fpc.Cov_End_Date) + 1 <= 0 THEN 1
            ELSE DATEDIFF(DAY, fpc.Cov_Start_Date, fpc.Cov_End_Date) + 1
        END
    ) AS rider_days,

    CASE 
        WHEN CAST(db.IsReider AS INT) = 0 OR mp.param_name = 'Base' 
            AND (CAST(fpc.IsPeriodicRider AS INT) = 0 OR fpc.IsPeriodicRider IS NULL) 
        THEN fpc.FixPrice 
        ELSE 0
    END AS base_premium_before_discount,

    CASE 
        WHEN (CAST(db.IsReider AS INT) = 1 AND mp.param_name <> 'Base') OR CAST(fpc.IsPeriodicRider AS INT) = 1 
        THEN fpc.FixPrice 
        ELSE 0
    END AS rider_premium_before_discount,

    fpc.FixPrice * COALESCE(fpd.pct, 0) / 100 AS discount_premium,

    (
        CASE 
            WHEN (CAST(db.IsReider AS INT) = 0 OR mp.param_name = 'Base') 
                AND (CAST(fpc.IsPeriodicRider AS INT) = 0 OR fpc.IsPeriodicRider IS NULL)  
            THEN fpc.FixPrice 
            ELSE 0
        END
    ) * (1 - (COALESCE(fpd.pct, 0) / 100)) AS base_premium_after_discount,

doc.dbt.__overview__.block_contents:
### Welcome!

Welcome to the auto-generated documentation for your dbt project!

### Navigation

You can use the `Project` and `Database` navigation tabs on the left side of the window to explore the models
in your project.

#### Project Tab
The `Project` tab mirrors the directory structure of your dbt project. In this tab, you can see all of the
models defined in your dbt project, as well as models imported from dbt packages.

#### Database Tab
The `Database` tab also exposes your models, but in a format that looks more like a database explorer. This view
shows relations (tables and views) grouped into database schemas. Note that ephemeral models are _not_ shown
in this interface, as they do not exist in the database.

### Graph Exploration
You can click the blue icon on the bottom-right corner of the page to view the lineage graph of your models.

On model pages, you'll see the immediate parents and children of the model you're exploring. By clicking the `Expand`
button at the top-right of this lineage pane, you'll be able to see all of the models that are used to build,
or are built from, the model you're exploring.

Once expanded, you'll be able to use the `--select` and `--exclude` model selection syntax to filter the
models in the graph. For more information on model selection, check out the [dbt docs](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/model-selection-syntax).

Note that you can also right-click on models to interactively filter and explore the graph.
